Papandreou Urges ‘Strong’ EU Decisions to Calm Bond Market

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   S t e a r n s
-- 
2011-03-11T10:17:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/papandreou-urges-strong-eu-decisions-to-calm-bond-market.html
Greek Prime Minister George Papandreou comments on the government’s program to reduce the  budget deficit  and on European Union efforts to stem the euro-
area debt crisis triggered by  Greece .  Papandreou, who spoke to reporters today in Brussels before
meetings of EU leaders, also comments on the Libyan civil war:  On Greek and EU debt-crisis policies:  “We are on track with our program. We have taken the pain
to make our economy viable, but now we need European decisions -
- strong European decisions -- to calm the market.”  On  Libya :  “Greece has been very active in the humanitarian efforts
to evacuate many nationals -- tens of thousands of nationals
actually -- from Libya to their home.  ‘‘Even today we had a successful cooperation with the Dutch
to help the Dutch extricate three of their members of the armed
forces and bring them back home to Holland.’’  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Stearns in Brussels at 
